Author:
Vol / Page: 18
Edition:
Quote: The most important [resolutions] are: (1) That in secondary schools all pupils not disqualified by age be given the opportunity of obtaining the proficiency certificate qualifying for free education; (2) that all now attending secondary schools who have passed the proficiency examination, and who have obtained scholarships be put on an equal footing with those eligible for free education next year, providing that they have passed the proficiency examinations, and are within the prescribed age.
